  <h1><span>January 6, 1941: State of the Union (Four Freedoms)</span>
</h1>


    <div class="share-trigger-mobile"></div>
</div>
<div id="block-mainpagecontent">
  
    
      <article role="article" class="presidential-speech">

  
    

  <div class="ps-container video-container">
    <div class="presidential-speeches--sidebar">
      
<div  class="about-this-episode">
    <h3>About this speech</h3>
      
<div  class="about-this-episode--inner">
      
            <p class="president-name">Franklin D. Roosevelt</p>
      
            <p class="episode-date">January 06, 1941</p>
      
  <div class="speech-location-container">
    <span class="speech-label">Location</span>
              <span class="speech-loc">National Archives</span>
          </div>

            <div class="about-sidebar--intro"><p>In his State of the Union Address, Franklin Roosevelt informs Congress of America’s responsibility to be concerned with Europe’s current conflict, the beginning stages of World War II, and the danger their allies’ assailants pose to the United States.&nbsp; To combat this potential threat, President Roosevelt suggests an “increase in armament production,” to be used in defense and/or to be supplied to European allies.&nbsp; Roosevelt says these actions, in addition to solutions for social and economic problems in the United States, are vital to preserving democracy and “four essential human freedoms” that he describes.</p>
</div>
      
  </div>
  </div>
    </div>

    <div class="presidential-speeches--body-wrapper">
     <a href="/the-presidency/presidential-speeches" class="back-to-listing--cta">Presidential Speeches</a> <span class="nav-separator">|</span> <label class="presidential-speeches--label">Franklin D. Roosevelt Presidency</label>
      <h2 class="presidential-speeches--title"><span>January 6, 1941: State of the Union (Four Freedoms)</span>
</h2>
      
<div  class="presidential-speeches--body">
      
            <div class="presidential-speeches--audio"><div class="audio-player">
    <audio height="100" src="https://web2.millercenter.org/speeches/audio/spe_1941_0106_roosevelt.mp3"
                            data-wave_color="#888888"
                                        data-prog_color="#E65400"
                            ></audio>
